) can be written in C/C++ or using DSLs and cross-compiled to WebAssembly. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.001022934913635254}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0002790093421936035}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0005080699920654297}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.004210412502288818}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9854488968849182}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.002575397491455078}}, "references": [{"label": "[2]", "normalizedForm": "[2]", "refKey": 2}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "WebAudio 2", "normalizedForm": "WebAudio 2", "offsetStart": 88, "offsetEnd": 98}, "context": "Videos show some demonstrations of these tools and a step by step tutorial for creating WebAudio 2 plugins is also available online . ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 2.8848648071289062e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.02832549810409546}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.017953038215637207}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 2.8848648071289062e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.02832549810409546}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.017953038215637207}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "WebAudio", "normalizedForm": "WebAudio", "offsetStart": 89, "offsetEnd": 97}, "context": "In 2018, with a group of researchers and developers (some of whom are members of the W3C WebAudio WG) we proposed a WebAudio Plugin standard (WAP) and gave birth to a growing ecosystem for the development of computer music applications in the browser [1].", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00021201372146606445}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9854488968849182}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0005173683166503906}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.004210412502288818}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9854488968849182}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.002575397491455078}}, "references": [{"label": "[2]", "normalizedForm": "[2]", "refKey": 2}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "code", "normalizedForm": "code", "offsetStart": 90, "offsetEnd": 94}, "context": "The AudioWorklet API, part of the WebAudio specification, required to run WebAssembly DSP code, is only publicly available on Chromium-based browsers (in this implementation, the choice not to have the audio thread with real-time priority can cause audio glitches in some circumstances, and is currently being questioned), while an experimental version is available in Firefox Nightly, this time with a real-time approach. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0014877915382385254}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00045222043991088867}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.000891268253326416}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8031065464019775}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.004647374153137207}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.004042446613311768}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "WebComponents", "normalizedForm": "WebComponents", "offsetStart": 91, "offsetEnd": 104}, "context": "This shows the maturity reached by recent Web APIs such as WebAudio, WebMIDI, WebAssembly, WebComponents and others. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.004210293292999268}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0002320408821105957}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.081031799316406e-05}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8031065464019775}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.35277318954467773}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.004042446613311768}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "WebAssembly", "normalizedForm": "WebAssembly", "offsetStart": 96, "offsetEnd": 107}, "context": "This is why we recently designed a new IDE for this language, which takes advantage not only of WebAssembly (the FAUST compiler itself was compiled in WebAssembly [7]), but also of other standards emerging from the W3C (PWA, WebMIDI, WebAudio, WebComponents, etc.).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 7.62939453125e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.35277318954467773}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.344650268554688e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8031065464019775}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.35277318954467773}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.004042446613311768}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "FAUST", "normalizedForm": "FAUST", "offsetStart": 113, "offsetEnd": 118}, "context": "This is why we recently designed a new IDE for this language, which takes advantage not only of WebAssembly (the FAUST compiler itself was compiled in WebAssembly [7]), but also of other standards emerging from the W3C (PWA, WebMIDI, WebAudio, WebComponents, etc.).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 7.62939453125e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.35277318954467773}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.344650268554688e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0004622936248779297}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.35277318954467773}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.9797234535217285}}, "references": [{"label": "[6]", "normalizedForm": "[6]", "refKey": 6}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "WebAudio Plugin", "normalizedForm": "WebAudio Plugin", "offsetStart": 116, "offsetEnd": 131}, "context": "In 2018, with a group of researchers and developers (some of whom are members of the W3C WebAudio WG) we proposed a WebAudio Plugin standard (WAP) and gave birth to a growing ecosystem for the development of computer music applications in the browser [1]. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00021201372146606445}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9854490160942078}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0005173683166503906}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9981180429458618}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9854490160942078}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0005173683166503906}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "code", "normalizedForm": "code", "offsetStart": 122, "offsetEnd": 126}, "context": "It also includes the WebAssembly version of the FAUST compiler, enabling developers to write, compile, run and test their code directly in the browser thanks to the WebAudio API.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0003151893615722656}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.004647374153137207}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.002575397491455078}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8031065464019775}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.004647374153137207}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.004042446613311768}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "FAUST", "normalizedForm": "FAUST", "offsetStart": 126, "offsetEnd": 131}, "context": "Many developers used to code native plugins in C or C++ have gotten into the habit of prototyping the DSP part with DSLs like FAUST [6].", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0004622936248779297}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001506805419921875}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.0728836059570312e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0004622936248779297}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.35277318954467773}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.9797234535217285}}, "references": [{"label": "[6]", "normalizedForm": "[6]", "refKey": 6, "offsetStart": 1480, "offsetEnd": 1483}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Chromium", "normalizedForm": "Chromium", "offsetStart": 126, "offsetEnd": 134}, "context": "The AudioWorklet API, part of the WebAudio specification, required to run WebAssembly DSP code, is only publicly available on Chromium-based browsers (in this implementation, the choice not to have the audio thread with real-time priority can cause audio glitches in some circumstances, and is currently being questioned), while an experimental version is available in Firefox Nightly, this time with a real-time approach. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0014877915382385254}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00045222043991088867}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.000891268253326416}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0018966197967529297}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0035463571548461914}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.16739189624786377}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Chromium", "normalizedForm": "Chromium", "offsetStart": 129, "offsetEnd": 137}, "context": "However, three commercial online Digital Audio Workstations have been online for more than one year now, running successfully on Chromium-based browsers, and will work on other browsers when implementations of the needed APIs will become available (polyfills are not always available).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00014281272888183594}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0035463571548461914}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.022397220134735107}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0018966197967529297}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0035463571548461914}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.16739189624786377}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Amped Studio", "normalizedForm": "Amped Studio", "offsetStart": 139, "offsetEnd": 151}, "context": "Some of the plugins we developed during the French research project WASABI are now sold as add-ons to an online Digital Audio Workstation (Amped Studio), showing the new opportunities that these emerging APIs have created.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001188516616821289}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.7841663956642151}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0019186735153198242}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00041681528091430664}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.7841663956642151}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.8119137287139893}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "WebAssembly", "normalizedForm": "WebAssembly", "offsetStart": 151, "offsetEnd": 165}, "context": "This is why we recently designed a new IDE for this language, which takes advantage not only of WebAssembly (the FAUST compiler itself was compiled in WebAssembly [7]), but also of other standards emerging from the W3C (PWA, WebMIDI, WebAudio, WebComponents, etc.).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 7.62939453125e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.35277318954467773}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.344650268554688e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8031065464019775}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.35277318954467773}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.004042446613311768}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "WebAudio", "normalizedForm": "WebAudio", "offsetStart": 165, "offsetEnd": 173}, "context": "It also includes the WebAssembly version of the FAUST compiler, enabling developers to write, compile, run and test their code directly in the browser thanks to the WebAudio API. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0003151893615722656}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.004647374153137207}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.002575397491455078}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.004210412502288818}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9854488968849182}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.002575397491455078}}, "references": [{"label": "[2]", "normalizedForm": "[2]", "refKey": 2}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "WebAssembly", "normalizedForm": "WebAssembly", "offsetStart": 168, "offsetEnd": 179}, "context": "Plugins can be written 1) in pure JavaScript, only using the high-level features of the WebAudio API, or 2) can be written in C/C++ or using DSLs and cross-compiled to WebAssembly. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.001022934913635254}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0002790093421936035}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0005080699920654297}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8031065464019775}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.35277318954467773}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.004042446613311768}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "WebAudio", "normalizedForm": "WebAudio", "offsetStart": 189, "offsetEnd": 197}, "context": "This online IDE facilitates the development of audio plugins to be deployed on different targets (different native plugin formats are supported) but we will focus here on the production of WebAudio plugins [2]. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 4.470348358154297e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.22660577297210693}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0008001923561096191}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.004210412502288818}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9854488968849182}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.002575397491455078}}, "references": [{"label": "[2]", "normalizedForm": "[2]", "refKey": 2, "offsetStart": 1956, "offsetEnd": 1959}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "http server", "normalizedForm": "http server", "offsetStart": 191, "offsetEnd": 202}, "context": "Tools are available to test plugins locally on the developer's machine before submitting them to the internal validation process set up by host app maintainers (plugins can be tried using an http server running on localhost, and can be seen by the host webapp), then the plugin is submitted for further validation, including manual checks. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.04713273048400879}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00043207406997680664}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0033890604972839355}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.04713273048400879}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00043207406997680664}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0033890604972839355}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "WebMIDI", "normalizedForm": "WebMIDI", "offsetStart": 225, "offsetEnd": 232}, "context": "This is why we recently designed a new IDE for this language, which takes advantage not only of WebAssembly (the FAUST compiler itself was compiled in WebAssembly [7]), but also of other standards emerging from the W3C (PWA, WebMIDI, WebAudio, WebComponents, etc.).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 7.62939453125e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.35277318954467773}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.344650268554688e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.004210412502288818}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.35277318954467773}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.16739189624786377}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SoundTrap", "normalizedForm": "SoundTrap", "offsetStart": 228, "offsetEnd": 237}, "context": "These WebAudio applications and tools show that online computer music applications can convincingly compete with their native counterparts, making easier some use cases such as collaborative music composition -as illustrated by SoundTrap being bought by Spotify and Amped Studio being offered to the 300 million users of NetEase Cloud Music a Chinese music social network (sort of Deezer/Spotify in 4 China). ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.000370025634765625}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.005937755107879639}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0002365708351135254}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.000370025634765625}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.005937755107879639}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0002365708351135254}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "WebAudio", "normalizedForm": "WebAudio", "offsetStart": 234, "offsetEnd": 242}, "context": "This is why we recently designed a new IDE for this language, which takes advantage not only of WebAssembly (the FAUST compiler itself was compiled in WebAssembly [7]), but also of other standards emerging from the W3C (PWA, WebMIDI, WebAudio, WebComponents, etc.).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 7.62939453125e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.35277318954467773}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.344650268554688e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.004210412502288818}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9854488968849182}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.002575397491455078}}, "references": [{"label": "[2]", "normalizedForm": "[2]", "refKey": 2}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "FAUST", "normalizedForm": "FAUST", "offsetStart": 237, "offsetEnd": 242}, "context": "This IDE supports multiple audio inputs (physical audio devices, MIDI interfaces, computer keyboard), different types of signal visualizations (spectrogram, oscilloscope, etc.), and generates a default GUI for testing the DSP coded (the FAUST language supports a set of primitives for describing abstract GUIs), as shown in Fig 1.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0003361701965332031}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 6.973743438720703e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.6689300537109375e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0004622936248779297}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.35277318954467773}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.9797234535217285}}, "references": [{"label": "[6]", "normalizedForm": "[6]", "refKey": 6}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "WebComponents", "normalizedForm": "WebComponents", "offsetStart": 244, "offsetEnd": 257}, "context": "This is why we recently designed a new IDE for this language, which takes advantage not only of WebAssembly (the FAUST compiler itself was compiled in WebAssembly [7]), but also of other standards emerging from the W3C (PWA, WebMIDI, WebAudio, WebComponents, etc.).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 7.62939453125e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.35277318954467773}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.344650268554688e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8031065464019775}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.35277318954467773}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.004042446613311768}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "webapp", "normalizedForm": "webapp", "offsetStart": 253, "offsetEnd": 259}, "context": "Tools are available to test plugins locally on the developer's machine before submitting them to the internal validation process set up by host app maintainers (plugins can be tried using an http server running on localhost, and can be seen by the host webapp), then the plugin is submitted for further validation, including manual checks. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.04713273048400879}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00043207406997680664}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0033890604972839355}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.04713273048400879}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00043207406997680664}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0033890604972839355}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Amped Studio", "normalizedForm": "Amped Studio", "offsetStart": 256, "offsetEnd": 268}, "context": "And this also opened up commercial opportunities: open source WebAudio software developed in the framework of academic projects such as the French ANR WASABI project, (guitar amp simulators, FX pedals, Rack plugin) are now being marketed as addons for the Amped Studio DAW.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00017982721328735352}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.17281591892242432}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0015154480934143066}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00041681528091430664}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.7841663956642151}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.8119137287139893}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Amped Studio", "normalizedForm": "Amped Studio", "offsetStart": 266, "offsetEnd": 278}, "context": "These WebAudio applications and tools show that online computer music applications can convincingly compete with their native counterparts, making easier some use cases such as collaborative music composition -as illustrated by SoundTrap being bought by Spotify and Amped Studio being offered to the 300 million users of NetEase Cloud Music a Chinese music social network (sort of Deezer/Spotify in 4 China). ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.000370025634765625}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.005937755107879639}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0002365708351135254}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00041681528091430664}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.7841663956642151}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.8119137287139893}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "WebAssembly", "normalizedForm": "WebAssembly", "offsetStart": 271, "offsetEnd": 282}, "context": "Not only several \"host\" applications have appeared, including commercial ones, but also tools to help developers, including an online IDE coded as a Progressive Web App (PWA) to write and publish plugins from A to Z, the audio DSP core of the plugins being compiled into WebAssembly. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001818537712097168}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.004746437072753906}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0016762614250183105}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8031065464019775}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.35277318954467773}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.004042446613311768}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Amped Studio", "normalizedForm": "Amped Studio", "offsetStart": 274, "offsetEnd": 286}, "context": "For example, developers can check that a plugin complies with the WAP specification, can check its main features, save/restore its state etc... Nevertheless, a publishing workflow is necessary before making a plugin available in a commercial online host application such as Amped Studio. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 9.524822235107422e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001709461212158203}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.013049900531768799}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00041681528091430664}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.7841663956642151}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.8119137287139893}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Firefox", "normalizedForm": "Firefox", "offsetStart": 369, "offsetEnd": 376}, "context": "The AudioWorklet API, part of the WebAudio specification, required to run WebAssembly DSP code, is only publicly available on Chromium-based browsers (in this implementation, the choice not to have the audio thread with real-time priority can cause audio glitches in some circumstances, and is currently being questioned), while an experimental version is available in Firefox Nightly, this time with a real-time approach. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0014877915382385254}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00045222043991088867}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.000891268253326416}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0014877915382385254}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00045222043991088867}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.000891268253326416}}}], "references": [{"refKey": 6, "tei": "<biblStruct xml:id=\"b6\">\n\t<analytic>\n\t\t<title level=\"a\" type=\"main\">Syntactical and semantical aspects of Faust</title>\n\t\t<author>\n\t\t\t<persName><forename type=\"first\">Y</forename><surname>Orlarey</surname></persName>\n\t\t</author>\n\t\t<author>\n\t\t\t<persName><forename type=\"first\">D</forename><surname>Fober</surname></persName>\n\t\t</author>\n\t\t<author>\n\t\t\t<persName><forename type=\"first\">S</forename><surname>Letz</surname></persName>\n\t\t</author>\n\t\t<idno type=\"DOI\">10.1007/s00500-004-0388-1</idno>\n\t</analytic>\n\t<monogr>\n\t\t<title level=\"j\">Soft Computing</title>\n\t\t